 <blockquote>
 What you are reading right now is a <B>response</B> -- and
 you'll notice that it starts with a line that shows
 
 <UL>
 <LI> its number (in this case, <B>2:1</B>
 since this is the first response to item number 2),
 <P>
 <LI>
 then the date and time the response was entered,
 <P>
 <LI>
 and then the name of the author (which is automatically added).&nbsp;
 The name is a link, which you can click on to learn more about
 the person.
 <P>
 
 </UL>
 
 <P>
 Next comes the <b>text</b> of the response; that is what you
 are reading right now.&nbsp;   It can contain ordinary text, or a
 mixture of text and <B>HTML</B>.&nbsp;   We'll learn more about
 putting graphics and other HTML data into a response a
 little later in this demonstration conference.
 </blockquote>
 
